{"meta":{"name":"Untitled","author":"ryan","version":"1.0"},"format":"node_tree","data":{"id":"a2f3eb2d4af95675","topic":"Schematics: Lunch and Learn","expanded":true,"view":"side","children":[{"id":"a2f3ebacfc95fbee","topic":"Schematics Overview","expanded":true,"direction":"right","theme":"theme-green","htmlContent":"<p>IBM Cloud Schematics provides powerful tools to automate your cloud infrastructure provisioning and management process, the configuration and operation of your cloud resources, and the deployment of your app workloads.</p><p><br></p><p>Schematics leverages open source projects, such as Terraform, Ansible, OpenShift, Operators, and Helm, and delivers these capabilities to you as a managed service. Rather than installing each open source project on your machine, and learning the API or CLI, you declare the tasks that you want to run in IBM Cloud and watch Schematics run these tasks for you.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p><a href=\"https://cloud.ibm.com/docs-content/v1/content/4614b49f9d30299a4d90f95d642161f1fe8a4388/schematics/images/schematics_architecture.png\" target=\"_blank\">Schematics Architecture</a></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>"},{"id":"a2f3f4855c1b0885","topic":"Workspaces","expanded":true,"direction":"right","htmlContent":"<p>Schematics workspaces deliver Terraform-as-a-Service capabilities hosted on IBM Cloud. The service allows you to automate the provisioning and management of IBM Cloud resources. If you need to stand up environments in other clouds, or roll out a multi-cloud deployment, sinply add your Terraform <a href=\"https://registry.terraform.io/browse/providers\" target=\"_blank\">provider</a> plugins to your Workspace and Schematics takes care of the rest.</p><p><br></p><p>### Workspace Flow</p><p>Getting started with Workspaces requires a few basic steps:</p><p><br></p><p><a href=\"https://cloud.ibm.com/docs-content/v1/content/4614b49f9d30299a4d90f95d642161f1fe8a4388/schematics/images/schematics_flow.png\" target=\"_blank\">Workspace Flow</a></p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong>Codify your IBM Cloud resources</strong></li></ul><p>Create HCL or JSON Terraform deployment files and store them in a version control system such as&nbsp;GitHub, GitLab, or Bitbucket.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong>Create your workspace</strong></li></ul><p>In this step we define the source repository for the deployment, pick our Terraform version, and add or update deployment variables.</p><p><strong>ï»¿</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Create an execution plan</strong>.</li></ul><p>Terraform works on the idea of state. You define your desired state (number of machines, load balancers, etc) and then Terraform creates an execution plan and describes the actions that need to be run to get to that desired state.</p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong>Provision your resources</strong></li></ul><p>When you are ready to make changes to your cloud environment, you can apply your Terraform configuration files.</p><ul><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><br></li><li><strong>(Optional) Enable continuous delivery</strong></li></ul><p>Connect a DevOps toolchain to your workspace, and enable IBM Cloud Continuous Delivery to automatically apply changes from your source repository to your resources in IBM Cloud.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>","theme":"theme-pink"},{"id":"a2f3efb9dec4f553","topic":"Actions","expanded":true,"direction":"right","theme":"theme-purple","htmlContent":"<p>Schematics actions deliver Ansible-as-a-Service capabilities to you so that you can automate the configuration and management of your Cloud environments.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>## Actions Flow</p><p>Getting started with Actions requires a few basic steps:</p><p><br></p><p><a href=\"https://cloud.ibm.com/docs-content/v1/content/4614b49f9d30299a4d90f95d642161f1fe8a4388/schematics/images/ansible_flow.png\" target=\"_blank\">Actions Flow</a></p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong>Add tasks to your playbook</strong>:</li></ul><p>Use Ansible YAML syntax to describe the configuration tasks that you want to run on your cloud infrastructure, such as installing software or starting, stopping, and rebooting a virtual server.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong>Create a Schematics action</strong></li></ul><p>When you create a Schematics action, you point your action to the repository that stores your Ansible playbook. Then, you select the cloud resources where you want to run the tasks that are defined in your Ansible playbook. To protect your cloud resources, you can further set up a bastion host in front of your target hosts that proxies all Ansible SSH connections to the target hosts.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong>Run your action</strong>:</li></ul><p>&nbsp;Schematics uses the built-in Ansible capabilities to connect to your target hosts via SSH, and execute the tasks that are defined in your Ansible playbook.</p>"},{"id":"a2f3fea9e0b16c9a","topic":"Portal Demo","expanded":true,"direction":"right","theme":"theme-yellow","children":[{"id":"a2f410dc5da17bdb","topic":"Workspaces ","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow","children":[{"id":"a2f400e7588aadc2","topic":"Create Schematics Workspace","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow"},{"id":"a2f403dddbfe49d4","topic":"Add default variables","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow"},{"id":"a2f4075bd28bee43","topic":"Create Plan","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow"},{"id":"a2f408d051701370","topic":"Apply Plan","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow","children":[{"id":"a2f40a9bd119e285","topic":"Verify and look output from UI/CLI","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow"}]}]},{"id":"a2f4160aa75fd477","topic":"Actions","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow","children":[{"id":"a2f4186459614187","topic":"Create Inventory from Workspace","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow"},{"id":"a2f41b25dd1ed186","topic":"Create manual inventory","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow"},{"id":"a2f42093e3fd2f4f","topic":"Add Playbooks","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow","children":[{"id":"a2f422fe5257d059","topic":"Add repo","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow"},{"id":"a2f425a8dcf525ba","topic":"Add env variables","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow"},{"id":"a2f427d2d3b579fa","topic":"Add inventory","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow"}]},{"id":"a2f42cc153891df9","topic":"Check and Run Playbook","expanded":true,"theme":"theme-yellow"}]}]}]}}